The paper deals with job scheduling, which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The use of posted prices to incentivize selfish jobs involves game theory (cs.GT) and mechanism design, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The analysis of the competitive ratio involves mathematical optimization and approximation algorithms (cs.LG), and the use of prices to influence job behavior involves information theory (cs.IT).
